
[1]gladness

   GLAD'NESS, n. [See Glad.] Joy, or a moderate degree of joy and
   exhilaration; pleasure of mind; cheerfulness.

   They--did eat their meat with gladness and singleness of heart. Act.2.

   [Gladness is rarely or never equivalent to mirth, merriment, gayety and
      triumph, and it usually expresses less than delight. It sometimes
                      expresses great joy. Esther 8.9.]
